title: Design a clean, innovative and modern logo for a professional consulting firm
slogan_to_incorporate: Bringing business and IT closer together
description:
Blueshift Consulting is a Canberra based small to medium enterprise (SME) that delivers professional services to the public, private and not-for-profit sectors. We are fully independent with no commercial ties to any local or international vendors so our customers can be assured that our advice is never conflicted by any external commercial or sovereignty ties to other organisations. We pride ourselves on having the optimal balance of a deep understanding, a structured approach and mature methodologies to deliver an optimised support environment, improved business and IT alignment and increased business value from IT.
Blueshift Consulting specialises in the following areas:
• Strategy, Planning and Strategic Advice
• Policy, Governance and Assurance
• Portfolio, Programme and Project Management
• Architecture and Technical Advice
• Business Analysis
• Service Delivery
Blueshift Definition: blueshift is the result of movement of a source towards the observer causing the visible light to “shift” towards the blue end of the light spectrum. For us, it means bringing our customers IT closer to their business.
other_notes:
• It is preferred that the logo/business name use anywhere up to two to three primary colours with a range of highlight colours that can be used in templates etc at a later stage (options for highlights are completely fine and don’t necessarily have to be included in the logo).
• The logo should have no background colour, i.e., be transparent.
• The colours and styles used in the logo must meet current WCAG 2.1 guidelines.
• The logo should be able to stand alone without the name of the company and/or slogan and the Logo/Company name should be able to stand alone without the slogan.
• Similarly, the name of the company and slogan should look good without the logo.
• If incorporated, the slogan should be able to be easily modified should it need to be changed.
• The logo must be suitable for use across multiple media types including documents, websites, business cards and possible other collateral such as polo shirts, coffee mugs and note pads etc.
• Do not be afraid of white space! It makes things cleaner and easier to read.
• The logo should lean more towards being simple as opposed to overly complicated.
• The design must be suitable and appealing to government organisations and private enterprises. I.e., nothing too outlandish, but doesn't have to be boring either.

Leeward in a nautical term meaning "out of the wind," which is fitting as our cafe is located on the water in a quaint fishing/sailing village on Vancouver Island, Canada. And you guessed it, the patio is out of the wind!
other_notes: We're located in Cowichan Bay, a unique and historic waterfront community on southern Vancouver Island, Canada. Here you'll find fishing boats and sailboats, seals and sea lions. Lots of docks and piers. A strong sense of community. A lot of summer tourists. Wonderful ocean. Amazing forests. A slower pace. A relaxed lifestyle. Our logo must be fitting of this. Nothing too modern or edgy. Nature prevails here. We want a welcoming logo that 'fits' our authentic seaside location with maybe a hint of vintage/nostalgic, but definitely not old fashioned. So, not too modern, and not old fashioned. 'Nautical' colors and visuals that match our seaside fishing village location. Perhaps ocean blue color(s), but something that easily translates to black and white too. We like the visual of a knot as it represents the tying down of boats and also represents strong community ties. We'd like a knot somewhere on the logo (We think! But you can show us other ideas too). A rope border around an oval or rectangular logo may also work, not sure. THE VISUAL is VERY IMPORTANT!! Just like Nike uses its swoosh without the word Nike, we envision using our simple visual (ie knot or other) as our "brand badge" on sandwich stickers and the like. We're excited to see your creative ideas! Thank you for helping to bring our vision to life! If you have questions, please email them to todd@truegrain.ca. Thank you, Todd
